'''Kostas Choumis''' ({{lang-el|<U+039A><U+03CE><U+03C3><U+03C4><U+03B1><U+03C2> <U+03A7><U+03BF><U+03CD><U+03BC><U+03B7><U+03C2>}}, {{lang-ro|Constantin "Costic<U+0103>" Humis}}, born [[September 18]], [[1914]] in [[Piraeus]], [[Greece]] - deceased [[1979]] in [[Athens]]) was a [[Greeks|Greek]]-[[Romanians|Romanian]] football player who played as a [[striker]]. He is often regarded in [[Greece]] and [[Romania]] as one of the greatest strikers in the 1930's<ref>{{cite news

    | url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/nationala/fotbalisti-care-au-evoluat-sub-tricolor-dar-s-au-nascut-in-afara-granitelor-romaniei-4047226
    | title=Fotbali<U+015F>ti care au evoluat sub tricolor, dar s-au n<U+0103>scut <U+00EE>n afara grani<U+0163>elor Rom<U+00E2>niei
    | work=Mediafax
    | author= 
    | accessdate=2009-03-13

}}</ref>.

== Club Career ==

Kostas Choumis made his senior debut in 1933, playing for [[Ethnikos Piraeus]], a team from his hometown. Shortly after his debut, he became a certainty for the starting lineup. He won the South Division championship with [[Ethnikos Piraeus]] in 1934-1935 season, scoring 15 goals in 10 matches<ref>[http://www.opadoi.gr/forum/index.php?topic=12651.0%3Bwap2 Evidence of Kostas Humis' appearances and goals for Ethnikos]</ref>. The National championship was not held in 1934-1935 season, but the next year it was played and Choumis became the top scorer of the league, with 12 goals scored in 14 matches<ref>[http://www.opadoi.gr/forum/index.php?topic=12651.0%3Bwap2 Evidence of Kostas Humis' appearances and goals for Ethnikos]</ref>.

In 1936, Kostas moved to Romanian club [[Venus Bucure<U+015F>ti]], after scoring two goals against [[Romania national football team|Romania]] a year earlier. He played his first match in [[Divizia A]] against Telefoane Bucure<U+015F>ti<ref> Mihai Ionescu, Mircea Tudoran ''Fotbal de la A la Z : Fotbalul mondial de-a lungul anilor'', Bucharest: Editura Sport-Turism, 1988</ref>. 

He remains in history as the first scorer for a romanian team in the European competitions, scoring the first goal of [[Venus Bucure<U+015F>ti]] in the First Round of 1937 [[Mitropa Cup]], against [[Ujpest FC]] from [[Hungary]]. The match was lost by Venus, 4-6, with Choumis scoring also the last goal of the romanian team.<ref>[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/europeancups/1937/venus_ujpest_budapest_01.shtml Venus - Ujpest, 1937 @ Romaniansoccer.ro]</ref>

Kostas Choumis won three times the [[Divizia A]] champion title, but din not win the [[Romanian Cup]]. He played in the last three matches of the 1940 [[Romanian Cup]] final, when, after two replays of the final (in the first replay, ended 4-4, Kostas Choumis scored himself a goal) [[Rapid Bucure<U+015F>ti]] won the third replay and the final<ref>[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/romanian_cup/1939_1940.shtml 1940 Romanian Cup final @ Romaniansoccer.ro]</ref>.

He remained at Venus during the World War II and in the first season after it, but left the team in 1947 to play at [[Gaz Metan Media<U+015F>|Karres Media<U+015F>]], where he played a season along [[<U+015E>tefan Dobay]]. He played for the Media<U+015F>-based team until 1950, and, after a short spell at [[UT Arad|IT Arad]], he retired from the playing career.

== International Career ==

Kostas Choumis made his debut for the [[Greece national football team]] in December 1934, in a Balkan Cup match against [[Yugoslavia national football team|Yugoslavia]]. A few days later, in a match against [[Romania national football team|Romania]], Kostas scored his first international goal.

In May 1935, in another [[Balkan Cup]] match against [[Romania national football team|Romania]], Choumis scored two goals and catched the eye of the romanian club [[Venus Bucure<U+015F>ti]]. In his last match for [[Greece national football team|Greece]], he scored the only goal for his team in [[Cairo]], but the Greeks lost the game against  [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]].

In 1941, after five years of living in Romania, Kostas made his debut for [[Romania national football team|Romania]], in a match against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]]. He scored the first goal for The Tricolours, and Romania won 3-2.

His last international match came in June 1943, playing another match against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]]. The match ended as a draw, 2-2.

